        -:   59:/* Extensions over POSIX bc.
        -:   60:   a) NAME was LETTER.  This grammar allows longer names.
        -:   61:      Single letter names will still work.
        -:   62:   b) Relational_expression allowed only one comparison.
        -:   63:      This grammar has added boolean expressions with
        -:   64:      && (and) || (or) and ! (not) and allowed all of them in
        -:   65:      full expressions.
        -:   66:   c) Added an else to the if.
        -:   67:   d) Call by variable array parameters
        -:   68:   e) read() procedure that reads a number under program control from stdin.
        -:   69:   f) halt statement that halts the the program under program control.  It
        -:   70:      is an executed statement.
        -:   71:   g) continue statement for for loops.
        -:   72:   h) optional expressions in the for loop.
        -:   73:   i) print statement to print multiple numbers per line.
        -:   74:   j) warranty statement to print an extended warranty notice.
        -:   75:   k) limits statement to print the processor's limits.
        -:   76:   l) void functions.
        -:   77:*/
        -:   78:
        -:   79:%token <i_value> ENDOFLINE AND OR NOT
        -:   80:%token <s_value> STRING NAME NUMBER
        -:   81:/*     '-', '+' are tokens themselves		*/
        -:   82:/*     '=', '+=',  '-=', '*=', '/=', '%=', '^=' */
